3 Sec. 1. Department of Education to amend rules. Resolved: That the
4 Department of Education shall amend its rules Chapter 60: New School Siting Approval,
5 Chapter 61: State Board of Education Rules for Major Capital School Construction Projects
6 and Chapter 125: Basic Approval Standards: Public Schools and School Administrative
7 Units to require standards governing air quality and ventilation for all newly constructed
8 public schools, including schools with mechanical and nonmechanical ventilation systems.
9 These standards must apply to all newly constructed public schools and must apply no
10 earlier than July 1, 2022 and no later than July 1, 2026. The rules adopted pursuant to this
11 section are major substantive rules pursuant to the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 5, chapter
12 375, subchapter 2-A, and the department shall submit the provisionally adopted rules for
13 final adoption to the Joint Standing Committee on Education and Cultural Affairs by
14 January 4, 2022 9, 2026.
15 SUMMARY
1166 This resolve amends Resolve 2021, chapter 114, which required the Department of
1177 Education to amend its school construction and siting and basic approval standards rules to
1188 require standards governing air quality and ventilation for all public schools. Instead, this
1199 resolve requires the department to amend its rules to require those standards for only newly
2200 constructed public schools.
